23/05/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Cedomir Jovanovic was re-elected on Saturday (May 21st) as leader of the opposition Liberal Democratic Party (LDP), telling delegates that Serbia needs to change its policy towards Kosovo and the region. 
Jovanovic reiterated that his party advocates membership in NATO. 
In his words, only LDP policies offer solutions to Serbia's problems. 
(Tanjug, Beta, B92, RTS - 21/05/11)
